@startuml PostApiIssueSequence

title Idempotent POST Issue - Sequence Retry Case

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825

autonumber

actor "Client" as client
participant "API Service" as api
database "Orders DB" as db

== Request #1 ==
client -> api : POST /orders\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
api -> db : INSERT order
api <-- db : OK (order_id=101)
... network timeout before response reaches client ...

== Request #2 (Retry of same intent) ==
client -> api : POST /orders\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
api -> db : INSERT order
api <-- db : OK (order_id=102)
api --> client : 201 Created (order_id=102)

note right of db
Issue:
Same business intent is processed twice.
Two rows are created because POST is not protected
with an idempotency key and response replay.
end note

note bottom
Impact:
- Duplicate orders
- Double charge risk
- Hard reconciliation for finance/support
end note

@enduml

